                "name": "Bible",
                "url": "/topics/bible"
            },
            {
                "name": "Slaves",
                "url": "/topics/slaves"
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "url": "/quotes/elijah_parish_lovejoy_729934",
        "quote": "Emancipation, to be of any value to the slave, must be the free, voluntary act of the master, performed from a conviction of its propriety.",
        "author": {
            "name": "Elijah Parish Lovejoy",
            "url": "/quotes/elijah_parish_lovejoy_729934"
        },
        "topics": [
            {
                "name": "Conviction",
                "url": "/topics/conviction"
            },
            {
                "name": "Emancipation",
                "url": "/topics/emancipation"
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "url": "/quotes/elijah_parish_lovejoy_729930",
        "quote": "It is not possible that one man can convert another into a piece of property, thus at once annihilating all his personal rights, without the most flagrant injustice and usurpation.",
        "author": {
            "name": "Elijah Parish Lovejoy",
            "url": "/quotes/elijah_parish_lovejoy_729930"
        },
        "topics": [
            {
                "name": "Injustice",
                "url": "/topics/injustice"
            },
            {
                "name": "Thus",
                "url": "/topics/thus"
            },
            {
